        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 348 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Melbourne, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Melbourne...                      Ash Flat...
Horseshoe Bend...                 Cave City...
Oxford...                         Franklin...
Sidney...                         Ballard...
Stella...                         Lunenburg...
Myron...                          Lacrosse...
Evening Shade...                  Maxville...
Zion...                           Violet Hill...
Sage...                           Larkin...
Brockwell...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
